{"keys":[{"id":"transformer-remark-markdown-ast-458b35911368ea8a3b8f12e343643e58-gatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypants","value":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"yaml","value":"title: Origins\ndate: September 18, 2016\ndescription: \"Hello, Pixels.\"\ndraft: false","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1,"offset":0},"end":{"line":6,"column":4,"offset":90},"indent":[1,1,1,1,1]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"ef-ful-gence\nnoun - a brilliant radiance","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":92},"end":{"line":9,"column":28,"offset":132},"indent":[1]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":92},"end":{"line":9,"column":28,"offset":132},"indent":[1]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Many people ask me what ‘effulgence’ means, and oftentimes they’re puzzled when I tell them it’s an english word. I admit that it’s not the most common word so I don’t expect people to know what it means anyway. I stumbled upon it when I was looking for english translations of the Sanskrit word ‘jyoti’ which means light. This was around 2011 when I was in search of an alias to release my ","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":134},"end":{"line":11,"column":392,"offset":525},"indent":[]}},{"type":"link","title":null,"url":"/music/","children":[{"type":"text","value":"music","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":393,"offset":526},"end":{"line":11,"column":398,"offset":531},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":392,"offset":525},"end":{"line":11,"column":408,"offset":541},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" with. Plus, it wasn’t taken by anyone else on SoundCloud! It’s stuck ever since and in many ways, it feels like it’s evolved to something much more than just a musical endeavor. I like to think of it as a pseudonym for creative output.","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":408,"offset":541},"end":{"line":11,"column":644,"offset":777},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":134},"end":{"line":11,"column":644,"offset":777},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"My journey in art began when I was 7 years old. At that time, I was living in ","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":779},"end":{"line":13,"column":79,"offset":857},"indent":[]}},{"type":"link","title":null,"url":"https://goo.gl/maps/dRHoHcJc5WJ2","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Kathmandu, Nepal","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":80,"offset":858},"end":{"line":13,"column":96,"offset":874},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":79,"offset":857},"end":{"line":13,"column":131,"offset":909},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" (where I was born). My father bought me a water color set and some paint brushes for my birthday. I was hooked. Painting brought so much color to my life, literally. I looked forward to getting home from school every day so I could go crazy on the back pages of my school notebook. The nuances of the paint brush taught me a lot. It forced me to loosen my hands up and to avoid being stiff, and in many ways that taught me a lot about life. At some point, I got a set of color pencils and started outlining my paintings with them. That’s when drawing started to take precedence over painting. It was a nice break from all the splatter. I started being precise and bold with each stroke. It was the perfectly opposite thing for me to learn. I was so into it that I even got published on the local newspaper!","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":131,"offset":909},"end":{"line":13,"column":938,"offset":1716},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":779},"end":{"line":13,"column":938,"offset":1716},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"html","title":null,"url":"./paper.jpg","alt":"Prayash Thapa Effulgence Art Newspaper","position":{"start":{"line":15,"