ition":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":92},"end":{"line":9,"column":28,"offset":132},"indent":[1]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Many people ask me what ‘effulgence’ means, and oftentimes they’re puzzled when I tell them it’s an english word. I admit that it’s not the most common word so I don’t expect people to know what it means anyway. I stumbled upon it when I was looking for english translations of the Sanskrit word ‘jyoti’ which means light. This was around 2011 when I was in search of an alias to release my ","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":134},"end":{"line":11,"column":392,"offset":525},"indent":[]}},{"type":"link","title":null,"url":"/music/","children":[{"type":"text","value":"music","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":393,"offset":526},"end":{"line":11,"column":398,"offset":531},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":392,"offset":525},"end":{"line":11,"column":408,"offset":541},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" with. Plus, it wasn’t taken by anyone else on SoundCloud! It’s stuck ever since and in many ways, it feels like it’s evolved to something much more than just a musical endeavor. I like to think of it as a pseudonym for creative output.","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":408,"offset":541},"end":{"line":11,"column":644,"offset":777},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":134},"end":{"line":11,"column":644,"offset":777},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"My journey in art began when I was 7 years old. At that time, I was living in ","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":779},"end":{"line":13,"column":79,"offset":857},"indent":[]}},{"type":"link","title":null,"url":"https://goo.gl/maps/dRHoHcJc5WJ2","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Kathmandu, Nepal","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":80,"offset":858},"end":{"line":13,"column":96,"offset":874},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":79,"offset":857},"end":{"line":13,"column":131,"offset":909},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" (where I was born). My father bought me a water color set and some paint brushes for my birthday. I was hooked. Painting brought so much color to my life, literally. I looked forward to getting home from school every day so I could go crazy on the back pages of my school notebook. The nuances of the paint brush taught me a lot. It forced me to loosen my hands up and to avoid being stiff, and in many ways that taught me a lot about life. At some point, I got a set of color pencils and started outlining my paintings with them. That’s when drawing started to take precedence over painting. It was a nice break from all the splatter. I started being precise and bold with each stroke. It was the perfectly opposite thing for me to learn. I was so into it that I even got published on the local newspaper!","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":131,"offset":909},"end":{"line":13,"column":938,"offset":1716},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1,"offset":779},"end":{"line":13,"column":938,"offset":1716},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"html","title":null,"url":"./paper.jpg","alt":"Prayash Thapa Effulgence Art Newspaper","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":1718},"end":{"line":15,"column":55,"offset":1772},"indent":[]},"value":"\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/73f7a99bab0c8f41e75d1f9185aa5bf8-d039f.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; z-index: -1; display: block; \"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 91.52892561983471%;position: relative; width: 100%; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Prayash Thapa Effulgence Art Newspaper\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/73f7a99bab0c8f41e75d1f9185aa5bf8-ec749.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/73f7a99bab0c8f41e75d1f9185aa5bf8-d894e.jpg 173w,\n/static/73f7a99bab0c8f41e75d1f9185aa5bf8-97c21.jpg 345w,\n/static/73f7a99bab0c8f41e75d1f9185aa5bf8-ec749.jpg 690w,\n/static/73f7a99bab0c8f41e75d1f9185aa5bf8-d039f.jpg 968w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    "},{"type":"text","value":"\n","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":55,"offset":1772},"end":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":1773},"indent":[1]}},{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Look ma, that’s me! The title literally translates to ‘Prayash’s Prayash.’ My name means attempt. So, I guess it’s an eloquent way of saying ‘The attempt of Attempt.’","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":2,"offset":1774},"end":{"line":16,"column":168,"offset":1940},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":1773},"end":{"line":16,"column":169,"offset":1941},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1,"offset":1718},"end":{"line":16,"column":169,"offset":1941},"indent":[1]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The sad part is, they never published the actual drawing. Just a profile on me.. lame. But, the validation felt assuring, and I promised myself to push farther and harder. But my dedicated slowly waned. I kept up as much crafts as possible, but I got too busy being a hooligan and playing video games to care enough about it.","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1,"offset":1943},"end":{"line":18,"column":326,"offset":2268},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1,"offset":1943},"end":{"line":18,"column":326,"offset":2268},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Fast forward to 11 years old when I heard my uncle strum the chords of ","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1,"offset":2270},"end":{"line":20,"column":72,"offset":2341},"indent":[]}},{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hotel California","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":73,"offset":2342},"end":{"line":20,"column":89,"offset":2358},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":72,"offset":2341},"end":{"line":20,"column":90,"offset":2359},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" by The Eagles in the other room. I walked over to see a massive dreadnought guitar in his embrace. There was something about those steel strings ringing together that caught my attention. Seeing my curious face, he generously offered to teach me a few chords. I learned the typical G -> D -> C progression while he sang ","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":90,"offset":2359},"end":{"line":20,"column":411,"offset":2680},"indent":[]}},{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Knockin on Heaven’s Door","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":412,"offset":2681},"end":{"line":20,"column":436,"offset":2705},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":411,"offset":2680},"end":{"line":20,"column":437,"offset":2706},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":". That felt so good. I was hooked! I couldn’t put the guitar down after that.","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":437,"offset":2706},"end":{"line":20,"column":514,"offset":2783},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1,"offset":2270},"end":{"line":20,"column":514,"offset":2783},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"html","title":null,"url":"./guitar.jpg","alt":"Prayash Thapa Effulgence First Guitar","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1,"offset":2785},"end":{"line":22,"column":55,"offset":2839},"indent":[]},"value":"\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/